  "description": [
    "19 V I E W S A N E V I E W S By INTERNATIONAL OFFICERS AND OF THE CIO Arthur L Garfield Int Rep UER and MWA A former Boston allAmerican football player Captain in the U S armed forces in North Africa writes back to his home town paper and reports that the boys are all interested in the box score not the basketball or foot ball box score but the box score in Russia This deep felt interest and re spect flows from the knowledge that they are fighting a common enemy an enemy of all civilized mankind and the respect shown by our soldiers for their Russian comradesinarms develops from the heat of battle against the com mon murderous enemy U S sold iers in North Africa now fight ing Hitlers storm troopers under stand and appreciate more than anyone possibly can just what the Russian soldiers and citizens have been up against during the past 23 months fighting this common en emy We have read of the mounting Russian box score but now on some battle fronts it is going badly The great Russian offen sive must have cost many thou sands of soldiers"
  ],
